==English==
===Formation===
Various [[possessive pronouns]] can be used for the middle word.  E.g. ''He spilled his guts.'', ''I spilled my guts'', ''They spilled their guts.''
===Etymology===
===Verb===

''(Slang)'' To confess, or to divulge secrets, typically speaking freely and at length after a change of motive or an incentive.

''At first, the suspect would not tell us anything about the other participants in the crime.  But after being offered a deal, he spilled his guts.''

